The paper deals with solving decision-making problems under uncertainty using probabilistic models and constraints. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a method to simplify the problem by identifying and exploiting identical subproblems, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the proposed method, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE).
